name: Drag Race Spain
overview: On the Spanish version of RuPaul's Drag Race, Supremme de Luxe presides as Spain's most talented queens compete to be crowned Spain's Next Drag Superstar.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: After much anticipation, international award winning RuPaul’s Drag Race finally arrives in Spain in the form of Drag Race España. Spanish Drag superstar Supremme Deluxe presides as ten of Spain's most talented queens compete over eight gruelling episodes to be crowned Spain's first Drag Race Superstar.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Start your engines! Season 2 is here! Drag Race España is back to find Spain’s next drag superstar! Each week the queens will be put to the test in numerous contests and challenges. Follow along to see who will survive the fierce competition and claim the crown!

episodes.name: ¡Bienvenidas a España!
episodes.overview: In this premiere episode, the queens arrive and take on their first challenge – mounting a bucking Spanish bull while posing for a photographer. Then their skills are tested to the max as they are tasked with designing and creating looks fit for the runway from everyday items from a typical Spanish market stall. Actor and international modeling icon Jon Kortajarena joins the creators of award-winning TV sensation Veneno - Javier Calvo, Javier Ambrossi and award-winning designer Ana Locking on the judging panel as the first queen sashays away from the competition.

episodes.name: Divas
episodes.overview: Supremme de Luxe continues to search for Spain's first drag superstar. After a fun pun with the Pit Crew, the pressure increases in the maxi challenge 'Divas', where the queens will have to work as a team and demonstrate their singing and dancing skills. The runway then fills with excitement as the queens pay tribute to La Veneno in front of their lifelong friend

episodes.name: Mocatriz
episodes.overview: The search for Spain’s First Drag Race Superstar continues. This week Supremme Deluxe tests the queens’ ball skills in a typically Spanish football challenge, then tasks them with creating their own advertising brand based on the Spanish concept Mocatriz – modelo/cantante/actriz (model/singer/actress). Almodovar actor and star of Spanish supergroup Ojete Calor (Asshole Heat) Carlos Areces joins the judging panel as a third queen leaves the competition.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: This week the queens’ growing friendships are tested as they read each other for the first time. Then it's the moment we've all been waiting for as Spain hosts its inaugural Snatch Game. And in a jam-packed episode the queens present no less than three runway looks in homage to the many looks of the women of Spain. Trap superstar Bad Gyal joins the judging panel as a fourth queen exits the competition.

episodes.name: The Art of Drag
episodes.overview: Working in pairs the queens get into the time-honored Spanish tradition of treading grapes in a barrel before they are tasked with treading the boards in their first-ever acting challenge based on one of Spain ́s most popular dramas. This week's runway is an homage to the world-renowned Spanish stars of the art world. Legendary Spanish Queen of Pop Alaska joins the judging panel as a fifth queen sashays away from the competition.

episodes.name: Drags de la Comedia
episodes.overview: Supremme de Luxe’s search for the first drag superstar of Drag Race España continues. This week, the queen must their comedy skills in a Roast where they will have to read the judges. For the challenge preparation they’ll count with the help of actor Brays Efe. This week’s runway is preparing for the Night of a thousand Rosalías. The humorist Susi Caramelo joins Javier Calvo, Javier Ambrossi and Ana Locking in the judges’ panel that alongside Supremme de Luxe, will have to announce the exit of another queen of the show.

episodes.name: Final Four
episodes.overview: With only four remaining, this week the queens once again put their dress-making and design skills to the test as they are paired with members of Spain's first inclusive rugby club Madrid Titanes in an emotional drag makeover challenge. Winner of Drag Race Holland Envy Peru joins the judging panel as all roads lead to the dramatic final.

episodes.name: Drag Race España Reunion Show
episodes.overview: All the queens are welcomed back for the first Drag Race España reunion show! They will review everything that has happened over the season, crown España's first Miss Congeniality, and look ahead to next week's grand finale!

episodes.name: Drag Race España Grand Finale
episodes.overview: In their ultimate challenge, the final three queens must shoot a video and perform a choreographed all-singing, all-dancing extravaganza to impress the judges enough to snatch that crown. The eliminated queens all return as the finalists face a final lip sync before Supremme crowns the series’ winner!

episodes.name: Reaction from the Queen: España Season 1
episodes.overview: In a bonus to the incredible first season of Drag Race España, we relive last week's revealing of the crowned queen to the three finalists.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: After much anticipation, international award winning RuPaul’s Drag Race finally arrives in Spain in the form of Drag Race España. Spanish Drag superstar Supremme Deluxe presides as ten of Spain's most talented queens compete over eight gruelling episodes to be crowned Spain's first Drag Race Superstar.

episodes.name: The New Presentation
episodes.overview: Season 2 kicks off with 12 new queens, an artistic first mini challenge, and a double runway.

episodes.name: Supremme Elegant Talent Extravaganza
episodes.overview: The library is open – already! And we put on our first ever Spanish talent show.

episodes.name: Putricia's Diary
episodes.overview: The queens get messy in the mini challenge – The Game of the Goose. And the tea is served on our chat show Diary of Putricia.

episodes.name: The Drag Calling
episodes.overview: It's our first ever musical – brought to us by our very own musical maestros Javier Ambrossi and Javier Calvo!

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: Wigs will fly in our poetry recital mini challenge then it’s the moment of truth with Snatch Game.

episodes.name: Spanish Ball - 10th, 20th and 30th Century
episodes.overview: We are throwing a Ball, and a construction challenge, and the theme is Spain across 3 centuries.

episodes.name: Come to Spain!
episodes.overview: The sumos are coming in our giant-sized mini challenge. And the queens create their own publicity campaigns to bring the thirsty post-pandemic tourists back to Spain.

episodes.name: Comedy Club Roast
episodes.overview: Everyone loves… Spanish puppets! And our comedy club queens roast some very special guests – the stars of season 1.

episodes.name: Golden Boys Makeover
episodes.overview: Don’t touch that! As our mini challenge enters the danger zone, we make over the gay retirees who founded Spain's first LGBTQ old folks' home.

episodes.name: The Reunion
episodes.overview: As we get ready for next week's Grand Finale, the queens return to discuss the season’s most memorable moments.

episodes.name: Take Me to Heaven
episodes.overview: The finale is here and an all-singing, all-dancing spectacle will help decide who is our next Spanish Drag Superstar!

episodes.name: The Coronation
episodes.overview: In a bonus to the incredible second season of Drag Race España, we relive last week's revealing of the crowned queen to the finalists.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Start your engines! Season 2 is here! Drag Race España is back to find Spain’s next drag superstar! Each week the queens will be put to the test in numerous contests and challenges. Follow along to see who will survive the fierce competition and claim the crown!

episodes.name: Spain is Different
episodes.overview: After transforming into farm animals, the Supremme Eleganza Talent Extravaganza returns to Drag Race España.

episodes.name: Drag Vision
episodes.overview: How much do you love Eurovision? The queens prove it with a geographical mini challenge and choreography maxi challenge. It’s time to Slo mo - mo - mo!

episodes.name: The Great Ball of Regions
episodes.overview: We are throwing a Ball and a construction challenge. The theme? Spain across their colors, flavors and traditional costumes.

episodes.name: Drag Sequels
episodes.overview: What is the best way to pop a balloon? The queens are divided into teams to face an interpretation challenge: Make a drag version of the best Spanish horror movies.

episodes.name: Snatch Game - España Season 3
episodes.overview: The library is open! Then it’s the moment of truth with the Snatch Game.

episodes.name: El Mago Precoz
episodes.overview: The queens star in a musical inspired by The Wizard of Oz and set in the Movida Madrileña in Madrid in the ‘80s.

episodes.name: The Second Chance
episodes.overview: A second chance is the perfect opportunity for the eliminated queens to return to the competition and shine: they will have to perform a comedy routine in pairs with the queens who are still in the contest.

episodes.name: One, Two, Drags!
episodes.overview: The queens do blind makeup in pairs and then recreate the mythical Spanish TV show Un, dos, tres, a delirious quiz contest with unexpected challenges.

episodes.name: Makeover: Barricientas
episodes.overview: Try not to laugh at the tortilla challenge before a very special makeover. Our contestants have to turn into authentic fairytale princesses, cleaning service workers, and those who take care of our streets and hospitals.

episodes.name: The Reunion
episodes.overview: The 13 queens of this third edition of Drag Race España talk to Supremme de Luxe about their time on the show and choose Miss Congeniality.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The four finalist queens have the opportunity to record a podcast with Supremme de Luxe. In order to become the winner, the queens create their own version of Supremme de Luxe’s “Fever” music video.

episodes.name: The Coronation
episodes.overview: The four finalists of season 3 have gathered to react live to the Grand Finale in a special episode presented by Samantha Ballentines!

episodes.name: Travel In Time
episodes.overview: The twelve queens face a Ball about their pasts, their futures and the rudemption for their first drag look in herstory.

episodes.name: Night of the Stars
episodes.overview: It's time for the Supremme Eleganza Talent Extravaganza!

episodes.name: Aquí No Hay Quien Diva
episodes.overview: The queens become characters of the hilarious sitcom ‘Aquí no hay quien viva’. On the runway they will showcase their worst nightmares.

episodes.name: I’m That Girl From School
episodes.overview: The queens are tasked with a choreography challenge. Then it’s the night of a thousand Ana Lockings!

episodes.name: Snatch Game - España Season 4
episodes.overview: The library is open! Then it’s time for the Snatch Game. Get ready to see the most rural looks on the runway.

episodes.name: Legendary Queens, The Musical
episodes.overview: Let’s pay tribute to Spanish Traditional Divas in ETERNALS, the musical.

episodes.name: La Draguería Del Coleccionista
episodes.overview: The puppets are back! The queens must create their own ads for the most exclusive teleshop on TV.
